l_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:1;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:21:\"Who is UgandaEMR for?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:215:\"<p>UgandaEMR is for people that need to implement a medical records system. It is both just a library of API calls and a database and a default implementation of those API calls in the form of a web application.</p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:2;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:29:\"How much does UgandaEMR cost?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:119:\"<p>UgandaEMR is a free, open-source program. All of the core resources needed are open source and freely available.</p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:3;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:30:\"Where is UgandaEMR being used?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:344:\"<p>UgandaERM is in about 340 sites across Uganda. Further implementations are underway in other locations locally.Nearly five hundredthousand discrete observations have been collected for nearly 1,000 HIV patients with over 55,000 encounters. We project by the end of 2016 we shall have over 1000 installations of OpenMRS across Uganda.</p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:4;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:27:\"Why should I use UgandaEMR?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:627:\"<p>At this stage, UgandaEMR requires a fairly sophisticated team of implementers to install and run.We are working toward a pre-built implementation that would allow more clinic sites to take advantage of a sophisticated, scalable EMR without needing the expertise to support and maintain it at a low level. UgandaEMR is backed by a data model driven by a concept dictionary, allowing for the collection of coded, reusable data without requiring changes to the data model. Furthermore, UgandaEMRis not based on an HIV-centric data model, so it can be adapted for use in tuberculosis, malaria, or general medical care.</p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:5;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:40:\"What technologies is UgandaEMR built on?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:334:\"<p>UgandaEMR is built on top of OpenMRS. Itis programmed in Java and the core application works through a web-browser. Hibernate is used as an interface layer to the database. Tomcat is used as the web application server. The back end database is currently in MySQL. The system creates HTML form entry modulefor form design.</p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:6;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:71:\"Do I need the Java SDK to run UgandaEMR? Or is the Java JRE sufficient?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:79:\"<p>The JRE is sufficient unless you are planning on doing code development.</p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:7;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:26:\"Where can I get UgandaEMR?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:162:\"<p>UgandaEMRis a work in progress. The <a href=\"http://github.com/METS-Programme\">source code</a> is always freely available for your review and download.</p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:8;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:47:\"What is the plan for new features in UgandaEMR?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:170:\"<p>We will post our plans on the <a href=\"http://wiki.openmrs.org/display/docs/Road+Map\">Road Map</a> page in the <a href=\"http://wiki.openmrs.org/\">OpenMRS Wiki</a>.</p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:9;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:47:\"Where can I see a working example of UgandaEMR?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:173:\"<p>Our <a href=\"http://aijar.mets.or.ug/\">demo</a> is a basic installation of UgandaEMRwith some common add-on modules and a sample patient data set. Try it out today!</p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:10;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"MYSQL skips during installation?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:333:\"<p>mysql doesnt skips during installation. This is common on HP Machines. This occurs due to issues in the computer registery. <a href=\"https://support.adminarsenal.com/hc/en-us/articles/220509507-Could-not-access-network-location-Hewlett-Packard-\" target=\"_blank\">Click on this link to get guidance on how to solve the issue</a></p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}i:11;a:3:{s:5:\"title\";s:42:\"What if my question isnt answered here?\";s:13:\"panel_content\";s:184:\"<p>Kindly drop us an email at<strong><a href=\"mailto:uganda-openmrs-support@gmail.com\">uganda-openmrs-support@gmail.com</a>.</strong>Someone will be in touch with you promptly.</p>\";s:29:\"panel_content_selected_editor\";s:7:\"tinymce\";}}s:12:\"_sow_form_id\";s:13:\"581b3e91134a1\";s:11:\"panels_info\";a:6:{s:5:\"class\";s:21:\"LSOW_Accordion_Widget\";s:4:\"grid\";i:0;s:4:\"cell\";i:0;s:2:\"id\";i:0;s:9:\"widget_id\";s:36:\"a26883e7-3772-4ad4-8711-7c0b3415642e\";s:5:\"style\";a:3:{s:27:\"background_image_attachment\";b:0;s:18:\"background_display\";s:4:\"tile\";s:10:\"link_color\";s:7:\"#dd3333\";}}}}s:5:\"grids\";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:\"cells\";i:1;s:5:\"style\";a:0:{}}}s:10:\"grid_cells\";a:1:{i:0;a:2:{s:4:\"grid\";i:0;s:6:\"weight\";i:1;}}}'),(1578,5366,'ptb_version','1.2.5'),(1579,5366,'ptb_size','23KB'),(1580,5366,'_edit_lock','1480495703:4'),(1581,5366,'_edit_last','4'),(1582,5366,'slide_template','default'),(1583,5366,'ptb_date','2016-09-27'),(1584,5366,'ptb_download','a:2:{i:0;s:8:\"Download\";i:1;s:90:\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/ugandaemr/files/1.0.14/databasebackup-1.2.5.omod/download\";}'),(1585,5240,'_panels_data_preview','a:3:{s:7:\"widgets\";a:6:{i:0;a:6:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"User Mannual\";s:4:\"text\";s:330:\"<p><a class=\"custBtn\" style=\"padding: 8px 30px 8px 30px;\" href=\"https://metsprogram.gitbooks.io/ugandaemr-documentation/content/\" target=\"_blank\">READ</a> <a class=\"custBtn\" style=\"padding: 8px 30px 8px 30px;\" href=\"https://www.gitbook.com/download/pdf/book/mets-programme/ugandaemr-documentation\" target=\"_blank\">DOWNLOAD</a></p>\";s:20:\"text_selected_editor\";s:4:\"tmce\";s:5:\"autop\";b:1;s:12:\"_sow_form_id\";s:13:\"584054a9283c2\